					<description><![CDATA[<img width="768" height="432" src="https://static.news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/us-national-debt-tops-gdp-for-first-time-since-wwii-768x432.jpg" class="attachment-medium_large size-medium_large wp-post-image" alt="" style="float:left; margin:0 15px 15px 0;" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://static.news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/us-national-debt-tops-gdp-for-first-time-since-wwii-300x169.jpg 300w, https://static.news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/us-national-debt-tops-gdp-for-first-time-since-wwii-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://static.news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/us-national-debt-tops-gdp-for-first-time-since-wwii-768x432.jpg 768w, https://static.news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/us-national-debt-tops-gdp-for-first-time-since-wwii-190x107.jpg 190w, https://static.news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/us-national-debt-tops-gdp-for-first-time-since-wwii-380x214.jpg 380w, https://static.news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/us-national-debt-tops-gdp-for-first-time-since-wwii-760x428.jpg 760w, https://static.news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/us-national-debt-tops-gdp-for-first-time-since-wwii.jpg 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" />The U.S. national debt has officially surpassed $38.9 trillion, eclipsing 100% of the country’s gross domestic product (GDP) for the first time since the end of World War II. This historic fiscal threshold offers a real-world validation for bitcoin’s 21 million fixed supply. Key Takeaways: U.S. national debt topped 100% of GDP for the first [&#8230;]]]></description>
		
		
		
